        - Service does NOT advertise before rules loaded
        - Service with no ES config serves immediately (open policy)

---

## Invariants

- A ResourceService with ES rules configured MUST NOT call sendResourceAdvertisement
  before rulesLoaded() is true.
- If a rule references an unknown operation name, the default behaviour is ALLOW
  (open by default, lock down specific operations).
- RuleSet signature MUST be verified before rules are applied; a tampered RuleSet
  is treated as an unavailable ES (retry).
- The retry loop runs on a background thread and is stopped cleanly on destruction.
- Encrypted transfer (encrypted_transfer.plan) can be layered on top of this plan:
  the GetRulesRequest / GetRulesReply are not themselves sensitive, but the ES
  login step (BeginEndorsementRequest with password) would use EncryptedPayload.

## Out of Scope

- ES-side rule authoring UI or DSL beyond the JSON config file
- Multi-ES federation (one authoritative ES per service type for now)
- Rule caching to disk (across restarts)
- Incremental rule updates (full RuleSet replacement only)
